-- Romania c.bank sees inflation hovering at record lows
-- By Luiza Ilie
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 09:43AM EDT
-- None



BUCHAREST, March 28 (Reuters) - Romania's inflation will likely cling to record lowsin the next months and risks to its outlook stem from volatile ca pital flows, deleveraging and changes in exposure to emerging markets, central bank Governor Mugur Isarescu said on Friday.

Isarescu told a news briefing after the bank's board decided to keep interest rates flat at a record low, the current 3.5 percent rate was "well positioned."